header.gameNote: HISPANIC COLLEGE FUND CLASSIC AT RALEIGH NC

article.headline: Delaware 77, The Citadel 57
article.story: RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- Zaire Taylor made all eight shots and scored 22 points in his college debut, Rulon Washington added 16 and Delaware held The Citadel to 27 percent shooting in a 77-57 victory Friday night in the Hispanic College Fund Classic. Harding Nana finished with nine points and 15 rebounds for the Blue Hens before fouling out in the opener for both teams. The final margin was very deceptive in a game that got ugly almost from the start. Because host North Carolina State played earlier, few fans were left from the announced crowd of about 8,000 for the opener. Those who stuck around saw a performance that hardly was ready for prime time. In the first half alone, the teams combined for 25 turnovers and five assists. Only three players scored for the Bulldogs, who shot 15 percent to trail 38-16. The final 20 minutes was more of the same. While Delaware finally found some rhythm on offense, The Citadel missed seven of its first nine shots and fell behind by 32 when Matt Hewson made a jumper, turning the final 13½ minutes into nothing more than garbage time. Demetrius Nelson had 15 points for the Bulldogs, while teammate Mark Schiavoni scored 11. And it won't get any easier for the military college from Charleston, S.C. -- it faces the Wolfpack on Saturday in the round-robin preseason event before playing Stetson the next day. At least the Blue Hens and coach David Henderson got a win out of it. Last season, they traveled to Ohio State for their first game and got beat 74-49. His sixth season began a bit more fortuitously, thanks to the defensive effort of his players. Delaware outrebounded The Citadel 54-38 to overcome 28 turnovers. Nana, who led the Colonial Athletic Association in scoring and rebounding last season, came up four rebounds short of his career high.
